"This image shows a 250 lb woman on the left and a 120 lb woman on the right. We can see weight gain from the outside, but we usually can't see what it's doing on the inside. Look at the fat surrounding the organs in the woman on the left. Do you also see the fat around her heart and around her brain? A little scary, isn't it? Look at the compression around the stomach and internal organs. Do you think that would have any impact on GERD and indigestion? Look at the compressed knee joints. Do you think those joints ache a little more than they should?" Losing weight isn't just about your image but also about your health, how your heart functions how your brain functions and how you feel and your body functions. Do it for better quality of life. Do it for your family, do it to extend your life.... I don’t care why you do it but I want you to find a reason to do it and JUST DO IT!!!

This is such a powerful picture. 😱We spend 💵💵💵💵 and ⏰ at... The nail salon getting a manicure and pedicure 💅🏻 The salon for hours getting our hair just the right color and cut 💇🏼‍♀️ The department store stressing over clothes that fit our bodies just right 👗

The spa getting facials and/or eyelashes that make our appearance more flawless 🧖🏻‍♀️ Ulta or Sephora getting the perfect makeup to “paint our face” 💄

BUT.... we say it’s “too expensive” to take care of our inside.  We spend hours at Target and TJ Maxx but say we cannot spend time at the gym.  We spend money on Amazon buying senseless things but say we cannot afford  supplements to make our bodies better. 🤦🏼‍♀️🙄😭 We spend massive amounts of money on the outside, the external, yet we say we cannot afford to go to the gym, take supplements, or eat clean. 🤔

Priorities folks.  You only get ONE body.  How long do you want it to last? 
You can rhinestone the peel of a rotten banana... but it’s still a rotten banana. 🍌🤮... #onebodyonelife
